						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/ACP-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/New-climate-change-research-partnership-in-Latin-America-and-the-Caribbean" title="New climate change research partnership in Latin America and the Caribbean" alt="link">New climate change research partnership in Latin America and the Caribbean</a></h2>

	
					<p>







 




  
  

	
	<a href="/var/knowledge/storage/images/media/images/caribbean-islands-maps/337726-1-eng-GB/Caribbean-Islands-maps.jpg" rel="lightbox[]" >	
	  </a>
	
	
	
	
  	






	 
  





	A new project on climate change mitigation and agricultural projects in Latin America and the Caribbean has been launched, which will bring together a consortium of research institutions and funders. The Government of New Zealand, the Inter-American Development Bank and the Regional Fund for Agricultural Technology (Fontagro, for its initials in Spanish) have signed an agreement to work together for the first time on a project to improve national greenhouse gas inventories and develop mitigation options in LAC. The research will be adapted to the farming conditions of each of the target countries: Argentina, Chile, Colombia, the Dominican Republic and Uruguay. (<a href="http://www.farmingfirst.org/2011/06/new-climate-change-research-partnership-in-latin-america-and-the-caribbean/" target="_blank">Farming First</a>, 8/6/2011)</p>
							<p><span class="date">1/07/2011</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/ACP-agricultural-S-T-dialogue/Related-developments/New-climate-change-research-partnership-in-Latin-America-and-the-Caribbean">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
